## Ars Electronica

### Metadata

```yaml
title: Ars Electronica
type: application/vnd.google-apps.document
created: 2019-09-08T09:07:18.749Z
modified: 2019-09-08T13:02:10.514Z
path: /My Drive/My Texts / Presentations/#PUBLISHED_DONE/Ars Electronica
id: 1YDl6rKx3GdOUXmSuRUkJ4T0zZ-7NGUifOvdK-aea46M
url: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YDl6rKx3GdOUXmSuRUkJ4T0zZ-7NGUifOvdK-aea46M/edit?usp=drivesdk
```

### Summary & Key Concepts

The document discusses how artificial intelligence (AI) is transforming creativity, science, and business by enhancing human creative capabilities. It highlights the natural human ability to think creatively through analogies and connections, which AI can augment by addressing the limits of human consciousness and learning. AI excels in scaling and can assist with intuitive and inspirational tasks through methods like pattern recognition and style transfer. The concept of 'Augmented Intelligence' is introduced, emphasizing the importance of AI tools that inspire and prioritize creativity.

**Key Concepts:**

- Creativity and analogy
- Limits of human consciousness
- AI in scaling and inspiration
- Pattern recognition and style transfer
- Augmented Intelligence
- Inspiration in AI tools
- Prioritizing creativity

### Full Content

```
﻿How Artificial Intelligence is Changing Creativity, Science and Business
* Creativity is the ability to think in analogies and put things together that are not connected yet.
* Our bodies and minds are really good at this. If you have kids, you know what I mean, right? These little humans are constantly bringing stuff together that does not seem to fit! But they create so much fun and beauty along the way!
* By the way, how many of you think that they are creative? How many wish they were more creative? How many of you think that creativity is valued by your employer or your colleagues at work? (I think most schools and company cultures are terrible at enabling creativity, but that is the topic of another talk!)
* So, if you think about it: our ability to be creative has two limits:
   * The number of things that we can hold in our consciousness
   * The ability to bring the right kind of things into proximity to one another so that we can connect them and thus be creative
* The first is a problem of scale. The second is a problem of learning about “the right kind of combinations”
* Machines are really good at scaling stuff, but can “machines” help us with the second problem, the stuff that is more like “intuition, gut feeling, inspiration, maybe even talent”?
* Let me give you a few fun examples of two methods that can used: Pattern recognition and Style Transfer
* So, this was a super quick ride through some of the stuff in AI and music that is out there. What you saw is the transition from creative to inspirational AI.
* When the AI helps humans with inspiration, I call it Augmented Intelligence
* Last Slide:
   * Let’s make sure that every tool we build has an “INSPIRATION NOW” button
   * Let’s make sure that we enable learning for machines on the data we already have
   * Let’s make sure that Creativity comes first.
```


