## What Business Leaders can Learn from Conductor Herbert von Karajan

### Metadata

```yaml
title: What Business Leaders can Learn from Conductor Herbert von Karajan
type: application/vnd.google-apps.document
created: 2016-09-16T15:46:02.384Z
modified: 2019-06-04T07:27:14.230Z
path: /My Drive/My Texts / Presentations/#PUBLISHED_DONE/What Business Leaders can Learn from Conductor Herbert von Karajan
id: 1-hzldw_8XhpL65PdwzB1KDxc6LefkjHToM1lv3HRs_I
url: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-hzldw_8XhpL65PdwzB1KDxc6LefkjHToM1lv3HRs_I/edit?usp=drivesdk
```

### Summary & Key Concepts

Herbert von Karajan, a renowned conductor, exemplified the importance of looking beyond one's industry for innovation, as demonstrated by his early adoption and promotion of the Compact Disc (CD) technology. By collaborating with Sony and other companies, he played a pivotal role in the CD's success, which significantly impacted the music industry and his career. His story underscores the value of collaboration, continuous skill improvement, and the pursuit of long-term goals to achieve visionary success.

**Key Concepts:**

- Cross-industry innovation
- Collaboration and partnerships
- Pioneering digital technology
- Long-term vision and goals
- Continuous skill improvement
- Impact of the Compact Disc on music industry
- Herbert von Karajan's legacy

### Full Content

﻿What Business Leaders Can Learn From Conductor Herbert von Karajan 
 
Look outside your own vertical for innovation that can help you grow your business or brand awareness.

Looking at an early prototype of the Compact Disc (CD) format in private home of Akio Morita, founder of Sony, Herbert von Karajan immediately saw its huge potential. He was quick to build a lasting collaboration with Sony, the inventor of the format. Not only did he record and publish the first piece ever with the new technology (An Alpine Symphony by Richard Strauss), he also invited Sony, Philips and Polydor to jointly present the CD at his own Easter Festival in 1981, thus creating a huge public interest and helping jumpstart the new technology. Finally, he convinced Sony to build its first and only European CD manufacturing plant in Anif/Salzburg, just around the corner from where he had built his family home. As a result, more than 10 Billion CDs were shipped from Salzburg in the years from x to y, and more than 3.000 people found work at the plant. And what was the immediate benefit for Herbert von Karajan? Being a pioneer of digital recording technology enabled him to sell more than 300 Mio records to this day, making him the most successful classical musician of all times with more records sold than the Rolling Stones. Also his name is forever linked to the greatest sucess of the music industry, the CD.


Find collaborators that will help you achieve your goals.


Truly great success can only be achieved when people with the same vision work together. There are no lone geniuses or visionary entrepreneurs who do it all by themselves. Herbert von Karajan knew that.


Work all the time to perfect your skills.
Set long-term goals for your vision
Do not change your vision to fit into reality, change reality to accomodate your vision


---

