```

### Summary & Key Concepts

The document emphasizes the transformative power of encouraging independent thinking through the phrase, 'I don’t know, what do you think?' This approach, attributed to Tom Kelly, fosters self-reflection, curiosity, and personal growth by valuing individual opinions and encouraging people to think for themselves. The author applies this philosophy in their work at the Karajan Institute and with startups, highlighting the importance of igniting passion and self-belief in others over merely possessing knowledge or skills.

**Key Concepts:**

- Encouraging independent thinking
- Transformative power of self-reflection
- Valuing individual opinions
- Igniting passion and self-belief
- Tom Kelly's philosophy
- Application in professional settings
- Curiosity and personal growth

### Full Content

﻿I don’t know. What do you think?


If you asked me for the quintessential Tom Kelly quote, I would say it is this: [read with open eyes, eyebrows raised and charming Southern twang] “I don't know, what do youuu think?”


Imagine every time you asked your professor something, he would respond: “I don’t know. What do you think?”


Imagine every time you asked your boss what she thinks and she would respond: “I don’t know. What do you think?”


Now imagine, that every time we heard this answer we would actually think about our own opinion, or go back and be curious about something, or take action, or simple pause and reflect on what could be. Imagine, how we would be transformed fundamentally as human beings, when everybody we encounter would take us seriously, would put worth on our opinion or would simply care about what we feel.


Every day when I get to work with my amazing team at the Karajan Institute, or with the many startups that pitch for me, I try to keep this lesson of Tom in my heart. It is not what we know or the skills we have that make us valuable. Much more important is the fire and passion we ignite in others, and that we spark their belief in themselves. 


The transformative power of thinking on your own terms is the most important thing I learnt from Tom and I thank him from the bottom of my heart for it!


---

## Computation and Music

### Metadata

```yaml
title: Computation and Music
