### Summary & Key Concepts

The document describes a comprehensive approach to analyzing unstructured business data from various sources, including regulatory filings, social media, and proprietary datasets. This data is used to assess the maturity levels of 500,000 companies in terms of their AI development, focusing on factors such as workforce, use cases, and financial investment. Machine learning techniques are applied to classify these companies based on their AI maturity.

**Key Concepts:**

- Unstructured business data analysis
- AI maturity classification
- Machine learning application
- Data triangulation
- Proprietary business data
- Company AI workforce and investment

### Full Content

﻿We are now reading the entire business internet, completely unstructured data, from SCC filings to financial regulatory filings to Tweets to every blog post, every job post, every conference visit, every power point, every video. So, it's really pretty comprehensive. We also have a lot of proprietary data around the business world, as to who's reading or viewing what ad, and we triangulate all of that in this graph and do machine learning on top to classify maturity levels of each company out of the 500,000 into how mature they are in AI. How many people do they have working, what are they doing with it, what are the use cases, how much money are they spending. That's how we built the study.


