```

### Summary & Key Concepts

The document emphasizes the importance of being open to innovation and staying informed about new technologies. It highlights the need to understand the music industry and related businesses thoroughly. It also discusses the significance of controlling the production and marketing processes of recordings and concerts, using Herbert von Karajan as an example of someone who ensured high-quality outputs by closely collaborating with engineers throughout the production stages.

**Key Concepts:**

- Openness to innovation
- Understanding the music industry
- Control over production processes
- Marketing of recordings and concerts
- Collaboration with engineers
- Quality perception of art

### Full Content

﻿1. Be open to innovation and learn about new technologies as they emerge.
2. Become Make an effort to understand the music and related businesses.
3. Control the production process and marketing of your recordings and concerts. Herbert von Karajan knew that the perception of his art depended on the quality of the recordings and the makeup of the products. To this end, he strove to achieve control over the production process, both by having the right to clear the finished product and, more importantly, by working closely with the engineers during all steps of the production.


