### Summary & Key Concepts

The 50th anniversary of the Easter Festival in Salzburg, founded by Herbert von Karajan, will be celebrated with a one-day conference focusing on classical music and technology. The event will include a classical music hackathon, panel discussions, and an innovation lab. The Karajan Institute aims to continue Karajan's vision of making classical music accessible to a young audience, highlighting its unique qualities and value. Planned activities include a hackathon challenge, classical music trivia, and a VR collaboration with Huawei and Dolby to enhance the classical music experience.

**Key Concepts:**

- Herbert von Karajan's vision for classical music
