### Full Content

```
﻿Proposed Karajan - HONOR Activities


In April 2017, Easter Festival in Salzburg will celebrate its 50th anniversary. The festival was founded by technology pioneer Herbert von Karajan as a platform for deep engagement, discussion and discovery around classical music. To celebrate the occasion,the Karajan Institute will host a one-day conference on classical music and technology that features a classical music hackathon, panel discussions and a curated innovation lab. www.karajanmusictech.com


The vision of Herbert von Karajan was to bring the beauty and sincerity of classical music to as many people as possible. Shortly before his death, Karajan said that he was born ten years too early, because "all the wonderful things that will come out of digital technology" he will not be able to see.


Today, the Karajan Institute continues this vision by bringing classical music to young audience worldwide, emphasizing the unique qualities of classical music and its value for young peoples’ growth.


Ideas:


* Invitation of Eva Wimmers to speak at the Karajan Music Tech Conference
* A “Karajan-Honor Challenge” for the Hackathon on the weekend before the conference. Winner to be announced at the event (live streaming, lots of press)
* A series of Classical Music trivia posts and related quizz to be published in anticipation of the event via our website and the brandnew and unpublished Karajan Classical Music Chatbot. The winner will receive an invitation to the Easter Festival to attend a concert, meet artists and connect with the Honor family
* A content collaboration for the upcoming release of the Huawei VR Gear. With an immersive experience based on the audio stems of the legendary Karajan productions. We have an ongoing partnership with Dolby to show our content in Dolby Cinemas and Dolby Atmos enabled cinemas. This would be our first venture into VR
* A Honor lounge with devices and headphones to listen to a selection of Karajan recordings
```


